---
import Layout from '../../layouts/Layout.astro';
import LessonNav from '../../components/LessonNav.astro';
import LessonAudio from '../../components/LessonAudio.astro';
---
<Layout title="Lesson 3: Best Practices">
  <div class="lesson-header">
    <span class="lesson-badge">Lesson 3</span>
    <h1>Best Practices</h1>
    <p class="lesson-subtitle">Essential formatting and writing guidelines for a professional portfolio.</p>
    <LessonAudio slug="lesson-2" />
  </div>

  <p>
    This lesson covers essential best practices for creating your Engineering Portfolio. 
    Following these guidelines will help you create a professional, easy-to-read document 
    that judges will appreciate.
  </p>

  <h2>Formatting Guidelines</h2>
  <p>Use consistent formatting throughout your portfolio:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Font</strong>: Stick to one or two readable fonts (e.g., Inter, Poppins, Montserrat)</li>
    <li><strong>Headings</strong>: Use a clear hierarchy: H1 for sections, H2 for sub-sections.</li>
    <li><strong>Font Size</strong>: 10pt minimum for body text, up to 18pt for headings</li>
    <li><strong>Line Spacing</strong>: Use 1.15 to 1.5 for readability</li>
    <li><strong>Margins</strong>: Keep them uniform; 0.5" to 1" is standard</li>
    <li><strong>Images</strong>: Always include captions and labels</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="callout note">
    <strong><svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="16" height="16" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" style="display: inline-block; vertical-align: -0.15em; margin-right: 0.25em;"><path d="M11 4H4a2 2 0 0 0-2 2v14a2 2 0 0 0 2 2h14a2 2 0 0 0 2-2v-7"></path><path d="M18.5 2.5a2.121 2.121 0 0 1 3 3L12 15l-4 1 1-4 9.5-9.5z"></path></svg>Remember:</strong> Judges spend limited time on each portfolio. 
    Make every page count by being concise and well-organized.
  </div>

  <h2>Visual Communication</h2>
  <p>A picture is worth a thousand words, but only if it's done right:</p>
  
  <div class="two-column">
    <div class="column do">
      <h4>✅ Do</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Use high-resolution images</li>
        <li>Include descriptive captions</li>
        <li>Add labels and arrows</li>
        <li>Show before/after comparisons</li>
        <li>Keep diagrams clean and simple</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
    <div class="column dont">
      <h4>❌ Don't</h4>
      <ul>
        <li>Use blurry or pixelated photos</li>
        <li>Leave images without context</li>
        <li>Overcrowd with too many visuals</li>
        <li>Use inconsistent styling</li>
      </ul>
    </div>
  </div>

  <h2>Common Mistakes</h2>
  <table>
    <thead>
      <tr>
        <th>Mistake</th>
        <th>Why It Hurts</th>
        <th>How to Fix</th>
      </tr>
    </thead>
    <tbody>
      <tr>
        <td>No page numbers</td>
        <td>Judges can't reference sections</td>
        <td>Add page numbers in footer/header</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Wall of text</td>
        <td>Hard to scan quickly</td>
        <td>Break up with headings and visuals</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Missing dates</td>
        <td>Can't verify timeline</td>
        <td>Date every entry or section</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Tiny fonts</td>
        <td>Strains readers' eyes</td>
        <td>Use 10pt minimum for body text</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>Inconsistent formatting</td>
        <td>Looks unprofessional</td>
        <td>Use a style guide and stick to it</td>
      </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Unlabeled images</td>
          <td>Judges don't understand context</td>
          <td>Always include captions and labels</td>
      </tr>
      <tr>
        <td>No margins</td>
        <td>Looks rushed and sloppy</td>
        <td>Use consistent margins (0.5" to 1")</td>
    </tbody>
  </table>

  <h2>Writing Style</h2>
  <p>Your portfolio should be professional but accessible:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Active Voice</strong>: "We designed a mechanism" not "A mechanism was designed"</li>
    <li><strong>Concise</strong>: Judges have limited time; get to the point</li>
    <li><strong>Define Terms</strong>: Explain technical terms the first time you use them</li>
    <li><strong>Use Bullet Points</strong>: Have lists instead of long paragraphs</li>
  </ul>

  <LessonNav 
    prev={{ title: "General Requirements", href: "/lessons/lesson-1/" }}
    next={{ title: "Team Overview", href: "/lessons/lesson-4/" }}
  />
</Layout>

<style>
  .two-column {
    display: grid;
    grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
    gap: 1rem;
    margin: 1.5rem 0;
  }

  .column {
    padding: 1.25rem;
    border-radius: var(--radius-md);
  }

  .column h4 {
    margin: 0 0 0.75rem;
    font-size: 1rem;
  }

  .column ul {
    margin: 0;
    padding-left: 1.25rem;
  }

  .column.do {
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.2);
  }

  .column.dont {
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.08);
    border: 1px solid rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.2);
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .column.do {
    background: rgba(16, 185, 129, 0.12);
  }

  [data-theme="dark"] .column.dont {
    background: rgba(239, 68, 68, 0.12);
  }

  @media (max-width: 640px) {
    .two-column {
      grid-template-columns: 1fr;
    }
  }
</style>
